# Translation Files

- Both `es.ts` and `en.ts` must have identical keys — TypeScript enforces this via `TranslationKeys` type
- Use dot-notation keys: `section.subsection.element` (e.g., `hero.cta.apply`)
- Brand terms remain in Spanish in `en.ts`: "Tinku", "Ritual CreAItivo", "Tu vIAje comienza aquí"
- When adding a new key, add it to BOTH files simultaneously
- Run `pnpm test` to verify parity (the `translations.test.ts` catches mismatches)
